[{"question":"What kind of response to the worst school shooting in American history is that?","answer":"Well, as you know, this is something the president as you know, feels really personally deeply about.","docId":"130408pmt","qSentId":42,"aSentId":43},{"question":"Isn\u0027t that what the president should now be doing?","answer":"Well, I think that is what the president has been saying to both members -- to both parties, and you know, the reality in the senate today is that the overwhelming majority of Democrats support background checks, and all we need is a small minority of Republicans in the United States Senate to join with the 90 percent of Americans to support doing this.","docId":"130408pmt","qSentId":54,"aSentId":55},{"question":"How would you sum up her tenure?","answer":"Well, I think I come from the opposite side of the political divide, if you like, being a labor prime minister.","docId":"130408pmt","qSentId":77,"aSentId":78},{"question":"Why was she so divisive?","answer":"Look, she took some very difficult decisions and she took decisions that were often extremely unpopular, so you know, even though over here in America, she would be I think admired probably both sides of the divide.","docId":"130408pmt","qSentId":84,"aSentId":85},{"question":"What was she like in private, Margaret Thatcher?","answer":"Well, the fascinating thing because obviously, I grew up in the sense politically with her as the prime minister, very distant figure.","docId":"130408pmt","qSentId":102,"aSentId":103},{"question":"Are you speaking as somebody who perhaps is in a similar position, a divisive reaction perhaps back home, but oddly popular perhaps in America as she indeed has proven to be today?","answer":"Look, I think part of the problem is in modern politics particularly, that if you\u0027re in power for any length of time, you take difficult decisions.","docId":"130408pmt","qSentId":111,"aSentId":112},{"question":"Rudy, she was quite something, wasn\u0027t she, Margaret Thatcher?","answer":"She sure was.","docId":"130408pmt","qSentId":141,"aSentId":142},{"question":"Why is that, do you think?","answer":"First of all, including by me.","docId":"130408pmt","qSentId":154,"aSentId":155},{"question":"Can you recognize that in somebody like her who was so consumed by the job and the power?","answer":"Sure.","docId":"130408pmt","qSentId":173,"aSentId":174},{"question":"What do you think her legacy should be, Rudy?","answer":"UILIANI: Well, I think revitalizing Great Britain.","docId":"130408pmt","qSentId":183,"aSentId":184},{"question":"This is going to be a big failure, isn\u0027t it, for President Obama if he can\u0027t do better than this?","answer":"First of all, we don\u0027t know what\u0027s going to happen.","docId":"130408pmt","qSentId":199,"aSentId":200},{"question":"I mean, should he be doing more of the Cuomo style of campaigning on this?","answer":"Well, I think what Cuomo did was he put together a very -- even a stricter gun control approach.","docId":"130408pmt","qSentId":233,"aSentId":234},{"question":"So you would encourage Republicans not to filibuster?","answer":"I would not only encourage it, I don\u0027t understand it.","docId":"130408pmt","qSentId":246,"aSentId":247},{"question":"How you doing?","answer":"Very well, thank you.","docId":"130408pmt","qSentId":268,"aSentId":269},{"question":"Niall Ferguson, as a fellow Brit, where does Margaret Thatcher rank in the pantheon of British prime ministers?","answer":"Second only to Churchill, I would say.","docId":"130408pmt","qSentId":289,"aSentId":290},{"question":"But where does she stand globally, do you think?","answer":"Oh, I would agree with Niall.","docId":"130408pmt","qSentId":299,"aSentId":300},{"question":"Would we be looking at Margaret Thatcher in a different way if she had been a man presiding over that period in Great Britain?","answer":"For the most part, not at all.","docId":"130408pmt","qSentId":319,"aSentId":320},{"question":"Was it fair?","answer":"Well, I have been enjoying your show not least because I heard a former editor of \"The Daily Mirror\" and a former Labor prime minister say positive things about Margaret Thatcher.","docId":"130408pmt","qSentId":347,"aSentId":348},{"question":"can I disagree with that?","answer":"Yeah, you can.","docId":"130408pmt","qSentId":391,"aSentId":392},{"question":"Is he doing the right kind of things with North Korea?","answer":"Well, I think we need to do more to help Japan right now and have a new American military strategy.","docId":"130408pmt","qSentId":442,"aSentId":443},{"question":"Niall Ferguson, guns and America, is there ever going to be a significant cultural change in America in relation to guns, do you think?","answer":"Well, I really wish there would be.","docId":"130408pmt","qSentId":461,"aSentId":462}]